<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>CSS Test: Table border resolution rules</title>
<link href="mailto:emilio@crisal.io" rel="author" title="Emilio Cobos Álvarez" />
<link href="https://mozilla.org" rel="author" title="Mozilla" />
<link href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1520138" rel="help" />
<link href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css2/tables.html#border-conflict-resolution" rel="help" />
<link href="reference/border-conflict-resolution-ref.xht" rel="match" />
<style>
  table {
    font-size: 2em;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    border: 5px solid green;
  }
</style>

</head><body><p>You should see no non-solid borders and no red.</p>

<table>
  <tbody><tr>
    <td colspan="4" style="border: 5px solid purple;">hello</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="border-top: 5px solid blue; border-right: 5px solid blue; border-bottom: 9px hidden red; border-left: 9px none;">one</td>
    <td style="border-top: 5px dashed blue; border-right: 5px solid blue; border-bottom: 5px outset red;">two</td>
    <td style="border-top: 5px ridge blue; border-right: 5px ridge red; border-bottom: 5px inset red;">three</td>
    <td style="border-left: 5px solid blue; border-bottom: 5px dotted red;">four</td>
  </tr>
</tbody></table>
</body></html>